From what I've read, saying what the various parts of the SCP are falls under the description category. Here's what I would put as the containment procedures:

Due to difficulty in containing SCP-277, it has been placed under a Level-█ lockdown. Activities of the citizens of SCP-277 and of SCP-277-1 must be monitored by no less than █ embedded agents, and civilians must not be aware of the Foundation or its involvement in monitoring SCP-277. Any attempts to contact civilians within SCP-277 by those outside SCP-277 must be investigated. Personnel must undergo psychological screening before being assigned to SCP-277.

The rest should be in the description, I think. Also, as a side note, we already have a city of missing persons, SCP-599. It could say that their information doesn't match anything on record, or something. Your call on that bit, really.

While I thought the interview was interesting and it did explain the second part of the article, it's not entirely necessary to expunge the fact that they were eating the sketches. It doesn't feel redaction worthy. Unless, of course, they're doing something worse, in which case you need to expunge a bit more so we can leave it up to our imaginations.

Feel free to disregard any of this; I don't think I have any more experience than you do.








